		<td class="main_font" width="100%">


								
								
			<!-- Begin News/Information Section -->
				<table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" ID="Table23">
					<tr id="trmasthead">
						<td valign="middle" class="main_font" align="center">
							<font size="3"><b>&nbsp;</b></font>
					    </td>
					</tr>
					
					   <td>

			
			
			


<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" ID="Table5">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
	
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" ID="Table6">
		<tr>

		
			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=531995">Shar Vahl</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>Belt of the Kala Dun</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Belt of the Kala Dun</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=570837"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:">Believeia</a> | 
		                        4/18/2002 1:37:35 PM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">I nearly pulled my hair out trying to figure out how to simply begin this quest.  Now that I've completed it, here's a more organized, step-by-step account for all the other poor souls who found this quest a bit confusing. <BR>
<BR>
First of all, I began this quest as a level 35 wood elf druid with indifferent faction towards the cat people. If you are not very familiar with Shar Vahl or Katta Castellum, it might be in your best interest to print a map from eqatlas.com. <BR>
<BR>
1. You MUST have better than indifferent faction with the cat people in order to even begin. I have seen many people mention here that the npc's quit talking after a few sentences. <BR>
In order to raise faction, I had to spend about 2 hours killing poachers and traders in Shadeweaver's Thicket. (note: while you are there, you can also save time by trying to forage a Luclin Clover.) Remember, the clover is NO RENT, so you must complete the quest before you log or you will lose the item. It only took me about 15 minutes to forage one. (sorry, I don't know what to tell you if you can't forage...I can't verify the other posters' claims of where to find one otherwise.) <BR>
<BR>
2. Upon your return to Shar Vahl, head to the potion shop to find Spiritist Ragnar. The shop is number 13 on the upper level of the Shar Vahl map. Hail him and say &quot;love potion&quot;. Next say &quot;what happened to Kanaad&quot;. Then say &quot;what were the results&quot;. Finally say &quot;what happened next&quot;. (if he won't talk to you through part of this conversation, kill some more poachers for better faction.) He will give you a tool box. (instead of running to Kanaad right away, hang on to the tool box until you've completed a few more steps) <BR>
<BR>
3. Next, head to the castle in Shar Vahl. Once inside, go down the hallway on the right and enter the last door. (room 1 on the lower level of Shar Vahl map) Kalila is lying on the bed. Hail her and say &quot;what love&quot; and then say &quot;what story&quot;. She will give you her diary. Make sure you bind yourself somewhere in Shar Vahl before you continue. <BR>
<BR>
4. Head to Katta Castellum. You might want to camo through some of the zones. However, there isn't much to worry about with the exception of Tenebrous Mts. (The dire sonic wolves see through camo.) Once in Katta, seek out Blaylock Geerlock. Like another poster mentioned, he is a gnome tinker on the bottom floor of the castle...follow the larger archways. Purchase a reflective shard from him. It'll cost you about 16pp. (fortunately, if you bound yourself, you can now simply gate back instead of trekking through TM again.) <BR>
<BR>
5. Now that you're back in Shar Vahl, head to the roof of the castle to the bard's guild. Hail Elder Hymnist Hortitosh and say &quot;essence of sonnet&quot;. He will act flattered. Give him the diary. You receive the essence of sonnet. It looks like a peridot. <BR>
<BR>
6. Now head to the corner of the roof. You will find Nayantara Tarana, the astrologer, on what looks like a gray stone look-out tower. Hail her and say &quot;drop of moonlight&quot;. She will ask for the reflective shard. Give it to her and she will give you the drop of moonlight. <BR>
<BR>
7. Next, return to the throne room of the castle. If you are facing the king, go down the steep set of stairs behind and to the right of you. Once you come to the room filled with several cat people selling shammy and bst spells, enter the door to your right. There you will find Kanaad. (room 8 on the lower level map) <BR>
He will not speak to you at all regardless of faction. Hail him and then give him the tool box and he will begin talking. Next, give him the clover, the essence of sonnet, and the drop of moonlight all at once. He will give you the love potion. <BR>
<BR>
8. Now you have to make the trip back to Tenebrous Mts. to &quot;kill&quot; Hobber. If you can, bind yourself somewhere in the cave and camo-up to avoid any possible ambushes from whatever doesn't see through it there. ;-) I found Hobber and his pet exactly where the other posters said he would be...in an alcove about 50 yards to the left of the Grimling Forest entrance near some rocks. I had to wait for what seemed like forever for the other mobs to leave. Most of the bats and dire sonic wolves were blue or yellow to me at 35. The vampires are definitely red. I finally figured I might as well try to begin. I attempted to root him, but he resisted. Then, I attempted the Expel Summoned spell on his pet...couldn't get it off. Then a vampire jumped in on the fun. Needless to say, it didn't work. Fortunately, I had bound myself at the entrance to GF. There I met a nice high level cleric who volunteered to rez me and help. <BR>
The cleric stayed at the entrance and I brought Hoober and his pet there. He feared the pet and I rooted and dotted Hoober. A few DD spells later, Hoober collapsed, but didn't die. <BR>
<BR>
9. Give Hoober the love potion and he will stand up and talk to you. Say &quot;what about Behari&quot; and he will give you the locket and despawn. <BR>
<BR>
10. Now the worst is behind you. If you decided to bind in the cave, you now have to run back to the castle in Shar Vahl. Go to the room with the girl who gave you the diary and hail her father, Jalil Talih. Give him the locket and he will give you the belt. Congrats! <BR>
<BR>
Once again, I will repeat another poster...if you are mid level like me, bring a friend to the brawl with Hoober. However, if you do try to do it alone, try leading him along the wall to the GF entrance like I did. There didn't seem to be nearly as many mobs nearby and if all else fails, at least you're closer to a zone. <BR>
<BR>
Hope this helps straighten out a few concerns. If you see me out and about, let me know if I can help you. Good luck to you all. <BR>
<BR>
Believeia Bearskins <BR>
Povar Server <BR>

			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
